## Summary
Lift recovered tools CLI crate (`byteport-cli`) into a PR branch, providing a developer CLI for codec, transport, UI, and upload operations via the `byteport-transport` crate.

## Context
This is the final step of E4 (lift recovered tools CLI to branch + open PR), following E3 which recovered the `byteport-cli` crate from stash-1. The crate exercises all `byteport-transport` port abstractions (codec, wire transport, terminal UI, mock UI, S3 upload) through a `clap`-based command-line interface.

## Changes
- **`crates/byteport-cli/`** — new crate with a `clap` CLI binary supporting 4 subcommand families:
  - `codec encode/decode` — hex encode/decode via `WireCodecAdapter`
  - `transport ping` — in-memory wire transport send/receive via `WireTransportAdapter`
  - `ui view/prompt` — terminal UI view rendering + mock prompt flow
  - `upload` — S3 upload instruction generation via `S3UploadTransport`
- **`Cargo.toml`** — added `crates/byteport-cli` to workspace members
- **`README.md`** — added work-state header section
- **`Cargo.lock`** — updated for workspace changes

## Testing
```bash
# Verify compilation
cargo check --package byteport-cli

# Run CLI help
cargo run --package byteport-cli -- --help

# Test individual subcommands
cargo run --package byteport-cli -- codec encode "hello"
cargo run --package byteport-cli -- codec decode "68656c6c6f"
cargo run --package byteport-cli -- ui view dashboard
cargo run --package byteport-cli -- upload my-file.txt --content-type text/plain --content-length 1024
```

